Letters written by Charles Dickens

&quot;Letters&quot;, cited by recipient and date in the References, are found in the Pilgrim edition, published in 12 volumes, from 1965 to 2003.

==External links==


Online editions
* David Copperfield read online at Bookwise
* &quot;David Copperfield&quot; at Internet Archive. Edition by Chapman &amp; Hall with preface by the author, and 40 illustrations by Phiz.
* &quot;David Copperfield&quot; at Project Gutenberg.
* &quot;David Copperfield&quot; – The original manuscript of the novel, held by the Victoria and Albert Museum (requires Adobe Flash).
* &quot;David Copperfield&quot;, at Bartleby.com (HTML w/ additional commentary)
* List of over 50 characters.

Adaptations
* 2022 &quot;Demon Copperhead&quot; a loose American modern adaptation of the novel, set in Appalachia, by Barbara Kingsolver
* 1950 &quot;Theatre Guild on the Air&quot; radio adaptation at Internet Archive
* 1947 &quot;Favourite Story&quot; radio adaptation at YouTube</text><links>
